\description{
The SAINT network for tabular data (Somepalli et al., 2021), ported from the official
implementation (\url{https://github.com/somepago/saint}).

Each numeric feature is embedded with its own two-layer MLP, each categorical feature is
embedded with a shared embedding table (using cumulative offsets), and a learned \code{CLS} token is
prepended to the resulting token sequence.
The token sequence is processed by a transformer that -- depending on \code{attention_type} --
applies self-attention over the \emph{features} of a row (\code{"col"}), over the \emph{rows} of a batch
(\code{"row"}, "intersample attention"), or both (\code{"colrow"}).
The final prediction is obtained by applying a two-layer MLP to the \code{CLS} token.

Either \code{task} or (\code{n_features_num}, \code{cardinalities}, \code{d_out}) must be provided.
}
\section{Intersample attention}{

For \code{attention_type} \code{"row"} and \code{"colrow"}, the representation of a row depends on the other
rows in the same batch. See the \emph{Intersample Attention} section of \code{\link{LearnerTorchSAINT}}.
}

